52 static void rename(GlobalValue *GV) { GV->setName(GV->getName() + ".old"); } 0
53 ----
54 // Upgrade the declarations of the SSE4.1 ptest intrinsics whose arguments have ----
55 // changed their type from v4f32 to v2i64. ----
56 static bool UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(Function* F, Intrinsic::ID IID, 0
57 Function *&NewFn) { ----
58 // Check whether this is an old version of the function, which received ----
59 // v4f32 arguments. ----
60 Type *Arg0Type = F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0); 0
61 if (Arg0Type != FixedVectorType::get(Type::getFloatTy(F->getContext()), 4)) 0
62 return false; 0
63 ----
64 // Yes, it's old, replace it with new version. ----
65 rename(F); 0
66 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), IID); 0
67 return true; 0
68 } ----
69 ----
70 // Upgrade the declarations of intrinsic functions whose 8-bit immediate mask ----
71 // arguments have changed their type from i32 to i8. ----
72 static bool UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(Function *F, Intrinsic::ID IID, 0
73 Function *&NewFn) { ----
74 // Check that the last argument is an i32. ----
75 Type *LastArgType = F->getFunctionType()->getParamType( 0
76 F->getFunctionType()->getNumParams() - 1); 0
77 if (!LastArgType->isIntegerTy(32)) 0
78 return false; 0
79 ----
80 // Move this function aside and map down. ----
81 rename(F); 0
82 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), IID); 0
83 return true; 0
84 } ----

454 static bool UpgradeX86IntrinsicFunction(Function *F, StringRef Name, 0
455 Function *&NewFn) { ----
456 // Only handle intrinsics that start with "x86.". ----
457 if (!Name.startswith("x86.")) 0
458 return false; 0
459 // Remove "x86." prefix. ----
460 Name = Name.substr(4); 0
461 ----
462 if (ShouldUpgradeX86Intrinsic(F, Name)) { 0
463 NewFn = nullptr; 0
464 return true; 0
465 } ----
466 ----
467 if (Name == "rdtscp") { // Added in 8.0 0
468 // If this intrinsic has 0 operands, it's the new version. ----
469 if (F->getFunctionType()->getNumParams() == 0) 0
470 return false; 0
471 ----
472 rename(F); 0
473 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), 0
474 Intrinsic::x86_rdtscp); ----
475 return true; 0
476 } ----
477 ----
478 // SSE4.1 ptest functions may have an old signature. ----
479 if (Name.startswith("sse41.ptest")) { // Added in 3.2 0
480 if (Name.substr(11) == "c") 0
481 return UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_ptestc, NewFn); 0
482 if (Name.substr(11) == "z") 0
483 return UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_ptestz, NewFn); 0
484 if (Name.substr(11) == "nzc") 0
485 return UpgradePTESTIntrinsic(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_ptestnzc, NewFn); 0
486 } ----
487 // Several blend and other instructions with masks used the wrong number of ----
488 // bits. ----
489 if (Name == "sse41.insertps") // Added in 3.6 0
490 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_insertps, 0
491 NewFn); 0
492 if (Name == "sse41.dppd") // Added in 3.6 0
493 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_dppd, 0
494 NewFn); 0
495 if (Name == "sse41.dpps") // Added in 3.6 0
496 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_dpps, 0
497 NewFn); 0
498 if (Name == "sse41.mpsadbw") // Added in 3.6 0
499 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_sse41_mpsadbw, 0
500 NewFn); 0
501 if (Name == "avx.dp.ps.256") // Added in 3.6 0
502 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx_dp_ps_256, 0
503 NewFn); 0
504 if (Name == "avx2.mpsadbw") // Added in 3.6 0
505 return UpgradeX86IntrinsicsWith8BitMask(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx2_mpsadbw, 0
506 NewFn); 0
507 if (Name == "avx512.mask.cmp.pd.128") // Added in 7.0 0
508 return UpgradeX86MaskedFPCompare(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_pd_128, 0
509 NewFn); 0
510 if (Name == "avx512.mask.cmp.pd.256") // Added in 7.0 0
511 return UpgradeX86MaskedFPCompare(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_pd_256, 0
512 NewFn); 0
513 if (Name == "avx512.mask.cmp.pd.512") // Added in 7.0 0
514 return UpgradeX86MaskedFPCompare(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_pd_512, 0
515 NewFn); 0
516 if (Name == "avx512.mask.cmp.ps.128") // Added in 7.0 0
517 return UpgradeX86MaskedFPCompare(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_ps_128, 0
518 NewFn); 0
519 if (Name == "avx512.mask.cmp.ps.256") // Added in 7.0 0
520 return UpgradeX86MaskedFPCompare(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_ps_256, 0
521 NewFn); 0
522 if (Name == "avx512.mask.cmp.ps.512") // Added in 7.0 0
523 return UpgradeX86MaskedFPCompare(F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512_mask_cmp_ps_512, 0
524 NewFn); 0
525 if (Name == "avx512bf16.cvtne2ps2bf16.128") // Added in 9.0 0
526 return UpgradeX86BF16Intrinsic( 0
527 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_cvtne2ps2bf16_128, NewFn); 0
528 if (Name == "avx512bf16.cvtne2ps2bf16.256") // Added in 9.0 0
529 return UpgradeX86BF16Intrinsic( 0
530 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_cvtne2ps2bf16_256, NewFn); 0
531 if (Name == "avx512bf16.cvtne2ps2bf16.512") // Added in 9.0 0
532 return UpgradeX86BF16Intrinsic( 0
533 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_cvtne2ps2bf16_512, NewFn); 0
534 if (Name == "avx512bf16.mask.cvtneps2bf16.128") // Added in 9.0 0
535 return UpgradeX86BF16Intrinsic( 0
536 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_mask_cvtneps2bf16_128, NewFn); 0
537 if (Name == "avx512bf16.cvtneps2bf16.256") // Added in 9.0 0
538 return UpgradeX86BF16Intrinsic( 0
539 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_cvtneps2bf16_256, NewFn); 0
540 if (Name == "avx512bf16.cvtneps2bf16.512") // Added in 9.0 0
541 return UpgradeX86BF16Intrinsic( 0
542 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_cvtneps2bf16_512, NewFn); 0
543 if (Name == "avx512bf16.dpbf16ps.128") // Added in 9.0 0
544 return UpgradeX86BF16DPIntrinsic( 0
545 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_dpbf16ps_128, NewFn); 0
546 if (Name == "avx512bf16.dpbf16ps.256") // Added in 9.0 0
547 return UpgradeX86BF16DPIntrinsic( 0
548 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_dpbf16ps_256, NewFn); 0
549 if (Name == "avx512bf16.dpbf16ps.512") // Added in 9.0 0
550 return UpgradeX86BF16DPIntrinsic( 0
551 F, Intrinsic::x86_avx512bf16_dpbf16ps_512, NewFn); 0
552 ----
553 // frcz.ss/sd may need to have an argument dropped. Added in 3.2 ----
554 if (Name.startswith("xop.vfrcz.ss") && F->arg_size() == 2) { 0
555 rename(F); 0
556 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), 0
557 Intrinsic::x86_xop_vfrcz_ss); ----
558 return true; 0
559 } ----
560 if (Name.startswith("xop.vfrcz.sd") && F->arg_size() == 2) { 0
561 rename(F); 0
562 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), 0
563 Intrinsic::x86_xop_vfrcz_sd); ----
564 return true; 0
565 } ----
566 // Upgrade any XOP PERMIL2 index operand still using a float/double vector. ----
567 if (Name.startswith("xop.vpermil2")) { // Added in 3.9 0
568 auto Idx = F->getFunctionType()->getParamType(2); 0
569 if (Idx->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) { 0
570 rename(F); 0
571 unsigned IdxSize = Idx->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(); 0
572 unsigned EltSize = Idx->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
573 Intrinsic::ID Permil2ID; ----
574 if (EltSize == 64 && IdxSize == 128) 0
575 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2pd; 0
576 else if (EltSize == 32 && IdxSize == 128) 0
577 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2ps; 0
578 else if (EltSize == 64 && IdxSize == 256) 0
579 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2pd_256; 0
580 else ----
581 Permil2ID = Intrinsic::x86_xop_vpermil2ps_256; 0
582 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Permil2ID); 0
583 return true; 0
584 } ----
585 } ----
586 ----
587 if (Name == "seh.recoverfp") { 0
588 NewFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(F->getParent(), Intrinsic::eh_recoverfp); 0
589 return true; 0
590 } ----
591 ----
592 return false; 0
593 } ----

1400 GlobalVariable *llvm::UpgradeGlobalVariable(GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
1401 if (!(GV->hasName() && (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_ctors" || 0
1402 GV->getName() == "llvm.global_dtors")) || 0
1403 !GV->hasInitializer()) 0
1404 return nullptr; 0
1405 ArrayType *ATy = dyn_cast(GV->getValueType()); 0
1406 if (!ATy) 0
1407 return nullptr; 0
1408 StructType *STy = dyn_cast(ATy->getElementType()); 0
1409 if (!STy || STy->getNumElements() != 2) 0
1410 return nullptr; 0
1411 ----
1412 LLVMContext &C = GV->getContext(); 0
1413 IRBuilder<> IRB(C); 0
1414 auto EltTy = StructType::get(STy->getElementType(0), STy->getElementType(1), 0
1415 IRB.getInt8PtrTy()); ----
1416 Constant *Init = GV->getInitializer(); 0
1417 unsigned N = Init->getNumOperands(); 0
1418 std::vector NewCtors(N); 0
1419 for (unsigned i = 0; i != N; ++i) { 0
1420 auto Ctor = cast(Init->getOperand(i)); 0
1421 NewCtors[i] = ConstantStruct::get( 0
1422 EltTy, Ctor->getAggregateElement(0u), Ctor->getAggregateElement(1), ----
1423 Constant::getNullValue(IRB.getInt8PtrTy())); 0
1424 } ----
1425 Constant *NewInit = ConstantArray::get(ArrayType::get(EltTy, N), NewCtors); 0
1426 ----
1427 return new GlobalVariable(NewInit->getType(), false, GV->getLinkage(), 0
1428 NewInit, GV->getName()); 0
1429 } 0

1431 // Handles upgrading SSE2/AVX2/AVX512BW PSLLDQ intrinsics by converting them ----
1432 // to byte shuffles. ----
1433 static Value *UpgradeX86PSLLDQIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, 0
1434 Value *Op, unsigned Shift) { ----
1435 auto *ResultTy = cast(Op->getType()); 0
1436 unsigned NumElts = ResultTy->getNumElements() * 8; 0
1437 ----
1438 // Bitcast from a 64-bit element type to a byte element type. ----
1439 Type *VecTy = FixedVectorType::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), NumElts); 0
1440 Op = Builder.CreateBitCast(Op, VecTy, "cast"); 0
1441 ----
1442 // We'll be shuffling in zeroes. ----
1443 Value *Res = Constant::getNullValue(VecTy); 0
1444 ----
1445 // If shift is less than 16, emit a shuffle to move the bytes. Otherwise, ----
1446 // we'll just return the zero vector. ----
1447 if (Shift < 16) { 0
1448 int Idxs[64]; ----
1449 // 256/512-bit version is split into 2/4 16-byte lanes. ----
1450 for (unsigned l = 0; l != NumElts; l += 16) 0
1451 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) { 0
1452 unsigned Idx = NumElts + i - Shift; 0
1453 if (Idx < NumElts) 0
1454 Idx -= NumElts - 16; // end of lane, switch operand. 0
1455 Idxs[l + i] = Idx + l; 0
1456 } ----
1457 ----
1458 Res = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Res, Op, ArrayRef(Idxs, NumElts)); 0
1459 } ----
1460 ----
1461 // Bitcast back to a 64-bit element type. ----
1462 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Res, ResultTy, "cast"); 0
1463 } ----
1464 ----
1465 // Handles upgrading SSE2/AVX2/AVX512BW PSRLDQ intrinsics by converting them ----
1466 // to byte shuffles. ----
1467 static Value *UpgradeX86PSRLDQIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Op, 0
1468 unsigned Shift) { ----
1469 auto *ResultTy = cast(Op->getType()); 0
1470 unsigned NumElts = ResultTy->getNumElements() * 8; 0
1471 ----
1472 // Bitcast from a 64-bit element type to a byte element type. ----
1473 Type *VecTy = FixedVectorType::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), NumElts); 0
1474 Op = Builder.CreateBitCast(Op, VecTy, "cast"); 0
1475 ----
1476 // We'll be shuffling in zeroes. ----
1477 Value *Res = Constant::getNullValue(VecTy); 0
1478 ----
1479 // If shift is less than 16, emit a shuffle to move the bytes. Otherwise, ----
1480 // we'll just return the zero vector. ----
1481 if (Shift < 16) { 0
1482 int Idxs[64]; ----
1483 // 256/512-bit version is split into 2/4 16-byte lanes. ----
1484 for (unsigned l = 0; l != NumElts; l += 16) 0
1485 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) { 0
1486 unsigned Idx = i + Shift; 0
1487 if (Idx >= 16) 0
1488 Idx += NumElts - 16; // end of lane, switch operand. 0
1489 Idxs[l + i] = Idx + l; 0
1490 } ----
1491 ----
1492 Res = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Op, Res, ArrayRef(Idxs, NumElts)); 0
1493 } ----
1494 ----
1495 // Bitcast back to a 64-bit element type. ----
1496 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Res, ResultTy, "cast"); 0
1497 } ----
1498 ----
1499 static Value *getX86MaskVec(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Mask, 0
1500 unsigned NumElts) { ----
1501 assert(isPowerOf2_32(NumElts) && "Expected power-of-2 mask elements"); 0
1502 llvm::VectorType *MaskTy = FixedVectorType::get( 0
1503 Builder.getInt1Ty(), cast(Mask->getType())->getBitWidth()); 0
1504 Mask = Builder.CreateBitCast(Mask, MaskTy); 0
1505 ----
1506 // If we have less than 8 elements (1, 2 or 4), then the starting mask was an ----
1507 // i8 and we need to extract down to the right number of elements. ----
1508 if (NumElts <= 4) { 0
1509 int Indices[4]; ----
1510 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) 0
1511 Indices[i] = i; 0
1512 Mask = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Mask, Mask, ArrayRef(Indices, NumElts), 0
1513 "extract"); ----
1514 } ----
1515 ----
1516 return Mask; 0
1517 } ----
1518 ----
1519 static Value *EmitX86Select(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Mask, 0
1520 Value *Op0, Value *Op1) { ----
1521 // If the mask is all ones just emit the first operation. ----
1522 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast(Mask)) 0
1523 if (C->isAllOnesValue()) 0
1524 return Op0; 0
1525 ----
1526 Mask = getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, 0
1527 cast(Op0->getType())->getNumElements()); ----
1528 return Builder.CreateSelect(Mask, Op0, Op1); 0
1529 } ----
1530 ----
1531 static Value *EmitX86ScalarSelect(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Mask, 0
1532 Value *Op0, Value *Op1) { ----
1533 // If the mask is all ones just emit the first operation. ----
1534 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast(Mask)) 0
1535 if (C->isAllOnesValue()) 0
1536 return Op0; 0
1537 ----
1538 auto *MaskTy = FixedVectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), 0
1539 Mask->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth()); ----
1540 Mask = Builder.CreateBitCast(Mask, MaskTy); 0
1541 Mask = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Mask, (uint64_t)0); 0
1542 return Builder.CreateSelect(Mask, Op0, Op1); 0
1543 } ----
1544 ----
1545 // Handle autoupgrade for masked PALIGNR and VALIGND/Q intrinsics. ----
1546 // PALIGNR handles large immediates by shifting while VALIGN masks the immediate ----
1547 // so we need to handle both cases. VALIGN also doesn't have 128-bit lanes. ----
1548 static Value *UpgradeX86ALIGNIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Op0, 0
1549 Value *Op1, Value *Shift, ----
1550 Value *Passthru, Value *Mask, ----
1551 bool IsVALIGN) { ----
1552 unsigned ShiftVal = cast(Shift)->getZExtValue(); 0
1553 ----
1554 unsigned NumElts = cast(Op0->getType())->getNumElements(); 0
1555 assert((IsVALIGN || NumElts % 16 == 0) && "Illegal NumElts for PALIGNR!"); 0
1556 assert((!IsVALIGN || NumElts <= 16) && "NumElts too large for VALIGN!"); 0
1557 assert(isPowerOf2_32(NumElts) && "NumElts not a power of 2!"); 0
1558 ----
1559 // Mask the immediate for VALIGN. ----
1560 if (IsVALIGN) 0
1561 ShiftVal &= (NumElts - 1); 0
1562 ----
1563 // If palignr is shifting the pair of vectors more than the size of two ----
1564 // lanes, emit zero. ----
1565 if (ShiftVal >= 32) 0
1566 return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType()); 0
1567 ----
1568 // If palignr is shifting the pair of input vectors more than one lane, ----
1569 // but less than two lanes, convert to shifting in zeroes. ----
1570 if (ShiftVal > 16) { 0
1571 ShiftVal -= 16; 0
1572 Op1 = Op0; 0
1573 Op0 = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType()); 0
1574 } ----
1575 ----
1576 int Indices[64]; ----
1577 // 256-bit palignr operates on 128-bit lanes so we need to handle that ----
1578 for (unsigned l = 0; l < NumElts; l += 16) { 0
1579 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 16; ++i) { 0
1580 unsigned Idx = ShiftVal + i; 0
1581 if (!IsVALIGN && Idx >= 16) // Disable wrap for VALIGN. 0
1582 Idx += NumElts - 16; // End of lane, switch operand. 0
1583 Indices[l + i] = Idx + l; 0
1584 } ----
1585 } ----
1586 ----
1587 Value *Align = Builder.CreateShuffleVector( 0
1588 Op1, Op0, ArrayRef(Indices, NumElts), "palignr"); ----
1589 ----
1590 return EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Align, Passthru); 0
1591 } ----
1592 ----
1593 static Value *UpgradeX86VPERMT2Intrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, 0
1594 bool ZeroMask, bool IndexForm) { ----
1595 Type *Ty = CI.getType(); 0
1596 unsigned VecWidth = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(); 0
1597 unsigned EltWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1598 bool IsFloat = Ty->isFPOrFPVectorTy(); 0
1599 Intrinsic::ID IID; ----
1600 if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 32 && IsFloat) 0
1601 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_ps_128; 0
1602 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 32 && !IsFloat) 0
1603 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_d_128; 0
1604 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 64 && IsFloat) 0
1605 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_pd_128; 0
1606 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 64 && !IsFloat) 0
1607 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_q_128; 0
1608 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 32 && IsFloat) 0
1609 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_ps_256; 0
1610 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 32 && !IsFloat) 0
1611 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_d_256; 0
1612 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 64 && IsFloat) 0
1613 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_pd_256; 0
1614 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 64 && !IsFloat) 0
1615 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_q_256; 0
1616 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 32 && IsFloat) 0
1617 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_ps_512; 0
1618 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 32 && !IsFloat) 0
1619 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_d_512; 0
1620 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 64 && IsFloat) 0
1621 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_pd_512; 0
1622 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 64 && !IsFloat) 0
1623 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_q_512; 0
1624 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 16) 0
1625 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_hi_128; 0
1626 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 16) 0
1627 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_hi_256; 0
1628 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 16) 0
1629 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_hi_512; 0
1630 else if (VecWidth == 128 && EltWidth == 8) 0
1631 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_qi_128; 0
1632 else if (VecWidth == 256 && EltWidth == 8) 0
1633 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_qi_256; 0
1634 else if (VecWidth == 512 && EltWidth == 8) 0
1635 IID = Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vpermi2var_qi_512; 0
1636 else ----
1637 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected intrinsic"); 0
1638 ----
1639 Value *Args[] = { CI.getArgOperand(0) , CI.getArgOperand(1), 0
1640 CI.getArgOperand(2) }; 0
1641 ----
1642 // If this isn't index form we need to swap operand 0 and 1. ----
1643 if (!IndexForm) 0
1644 std::swap(Args[0], Args[1]); 0
1645 ----
1646 Value *V = Builder.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID), 0
1647 Args); ----
1648 Value *PassThru = ZeroMask ? ConstantAggregateZero::get(Ty) 0
1649 : Builder.CreateBitCast(CI.getArgOperand(1), 0
1650 Ty); 0
1651 return EmitX86Select(Builder, CI.getArgOperand(3), V, PassThru); 0
1652 } ----

1654 static Value *UpgradeX86BinaryIntrinsics(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, 0
1655 Intrinsic::ID IID) { ----
1656 Type *Ty = CI.getType(); 0
1657 Value *Op0 = CI.getOperand(0); 0
1658 Value *Op1 = CI.getOperand(1); 0
1659 Function *Intrin = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID, Ty); 0
1660 Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(Intrin, {Op0, Op1}); 0
1661 ----
1662 if (CI.arg_size() == 4) { // For masked intrinsics. 0
1663 Value *VecSrc = CI.getOperand(2); 0
1664 Value *Mask = CI.getOperand(3); 0
1665 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Res, VecSrc); 0
1666 } ----
1667 return Res; 0

1670 static Value *upgradeX86Rotate(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, 0
1671 bool IsRotateRight) { ----
1672 Type *Ty = CI.getType(); 0
1673 Value *Src = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1674 Value *Amt = CI.getArgOperand(1); 0
1675 ----
1676 // Amount may be scalar immediate, in which case create a splat vector. ----
1677 // Funnel shifts amounts are treated as modulo and types are all power-of-2 so ----
1678 // we only care about the lowest log2 bits anyway. ----
1679 if (Amt->getType() != Ty) { 0
1680 unsigned NumElts = cast(Ty)->getNumElements(); 0
1681 Amt = Builder.CreateIntCast(Amt, Ty->getScalarType(), false); 0
1682 Amt = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElts, Amt); 0
1683 } ----
1684 ----
1685 Intrinsic::ID IID = IsRotateRight ? Intrinsic::fshr : Intrinsic::fshl; 0
1686 Function *Intrin = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID, Ty); 0
1687 Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(Intrin, {Src, Src, Amt}); 0
1688 ----
1689 if (CI.arg_size() == 4) { // For masked intrinsics. 0
1690 Value *VecSrc = CI.getOperand(2); 0
1691 Value *Mask = CI.getOperand(3); 0
1692 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Res, VecSrc); 0
1693 } ----
1694 return Res; 0
1695 } ----
1696 ----
1697 static Value *upgradeX86vpcom(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, unsigned Imm, 0
1698 bool IsSigned) { ----
1699 Type *Ty = CI.getType(); 0
1700 Value *LHS = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1701 Value *RHS = CI.getArgOperand(1); 0
1702 ----
1703 CmpInst::Predicate Pred; ----
1704 switch (Imm) { 0
1705 case 0x0: 0
1706 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT; 0
1707 break; 0
1708 case 0x1: 0
1709 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE; 0
1710 break; 0
1711 case 0x2: 0
1712 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT; 0
1713 break; 0
1714 case 0x3: 0
1715 Pred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE; 0
1716 break; 0
1717 case 0x4: 0
1718 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ; 0
1719 break; 0
1720 case 0x5: 0
1721 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE; 0
1722 break; 0
1723 case 0x6: 0
1724 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty); // FALSE 0
1725 case 0x7: 0
1726 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty); // TRUE 0
1727 default: 0
1728 llvm_unreachable("Unknown XOP vpcom/vpcomu predicate"); 0
1729 } ----
1730 ----
1731 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, LHS, RHS); 0
1732 Value *Ext = Builder.CreateSExt(Cmp, Ty); 0
1733 return Ext; 0
1734 } ----
1735 ----
1736 static Value *upgradeX86ConcatShift(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, 0
1737 bool IsShiftRight, bool ZeroMask) { ----
1738 Type *Ty = CI.getType(); 0
1739 Value *Op0 = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1740 Value *Op1 = CI.getArgOperand(1); 0
1741 Value *Amt = CI.getArgOperand(2); 0
1742 ----
1743 if (IsShiftRight) 0
1744 std::swap(Op0, Op1); 0
1745 ----
1746 // Amount may be scalar immediate, in which case create a splat vector. ----
1747 // Funnel shifts amounts are treated as modulo and types are all power-of-2 so ----
1748 // we only care about the lowest log2 bits anyway. ----
1749 if (Amt->getType() != Ty) { 0
1750 unsigned NumElts = cast(Ty)->getNumElements(); 0
1751 Amt = Builder.CreateIntCast(Amt, Ty->getScalarType(), false); 0
1752 Amt = Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElts, Amt); 0
1753 } ----
1754 ----
1755 Intrinsic::ID IID = IsShiftRight ? Intrinsic::fshr : Intrinsic::fshl; 0
1756 Function *Intrin = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID, Ty); 0
1757 Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(Intrin, {Op0, Op1, Amt}); 0
1758 ----
1759 unsigned NumArgs = CI.arg_size(); 0
1760 if (NumArgs >= 4) { // For masked intrinsics. 0
1761 Value *VecSrc = NumArgs == 5 ? CI.getArgOperand(3) : 0
1762 ZeroMask ? ConstantAggregateZero::get(CI.getType()) : 0
1763 CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1764 Value *Mask = CI.getOperand(NumArgs - 1); 0
1765 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, Mask, Res, VecSrc); 0
1766 } ----
1767 return Res; 0
1768 } ----
1769 ----
1770 static Value *UpgradeMaskedStore(IRBuilder<> &Builder, 0
1771 Value *Ptr, Value *Data, Value *Mask, ----
1772 bool Aligned) { ----
1773 // Cast the pointer to the right type. ----
1774 Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, 0
1775 llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(Data->getType())); 0
1776 const Align Alignment = ----
1777 Aligned ----
1778 ? Align(Data->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedValue() / 8) 0
1779 : Align(1); 0
1780 ----
1781 // If the mask is all ones just emit a regular store. ----
1782 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast(Mask)) 0
1783 if (C->isAllOnesValue()) 0
1784 return Builder.CreateAlignedStore(Data, Ptr, Alignment); 0
1785 ----
1786 // Convert the mask from an integer type to a vector of i1. ----
1787 unsigned NumElts = cast(Data->getType())->getNumElements(); 0
1788 Mask = getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, NumElts); 0
1789 return Builder.CreateMaskedStore(Data, Ptr, Alignment, Mask); 0
1790 } ----
1791 ----
1792 static Value *UpgradeMaskedLoad(IRBuilder<> &Builder, 0
1793 Value *Ptr, Value *Passthru, Value *Mask, ----
1794 bool Aligned) { ----
1795 Type *ValTy = Passthru->getType(); 0
1796 // Cast the pointer to the right type. ----
1797 Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(ValTy)); 0
1798 const Align Alignment = ----
1799 Aligned ----
1800 ? Align( ----
1801 Passthru->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedValue() / 0
1802 8) ----
1803 : Align(1); 0
1804 ----
1805 // If the mask is all ones just emit a regular store. ----
1806 if (const auto *C = dyn_cast(Mask)) 0
1807 if (C->isAllOnesValue()) 0
1808 return Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(ValTy, Ptr, Alignment); 0
1809 ----
1810 // Convert the mask from an integer type to a vector of i1. ----
1811 unsigned NumElts = cast(ValTy)->getNumElements(); 0
1812 Mask = getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, NumElts); 0
1813 return Builder.CreateMaskedLoad(ValTy, Ptr, Alignment, Mask, Passthru); 0
1814 } ----
1815 ----
1816 static Value *upgradeAbs(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI) { 0
1817 Type *Ty = CI.getType(); 0
1818 Value *Op0 = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1819 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), Intrinsic::abs, Ty); 0
1820 Value *Res = Builder.CreateCall(F, {Op0, Builder.getInt1(false)}); 0
1821 if (CI.arg_size() == 3) 0
1822 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, CI.getArgOperand(2), Res, CI.getArgOperand(1)); 0
1823 return Res; 0
1824 } ----
1825 ----
1826 static Value *upgradePMULDQ(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, bool IsSigned) { 0
1827 Type *Ty = CI.getType(); 0
1828 ----
1829 // Arguments have a vXi32 type so cast to vXi64. ----
1830 Value *LHS = Builder.CreateBitCast(CI.getArgOperand(0), Ty); 0
1831 Value *RHS = Builder.CreateBitCast(CI.getArgOperand(1), Ty); 0
1832 ----
1833 if (IsSigned) { 0
1834 // Shift left then arithmetic shift right. ----
1835 Constant *ShiftAmt = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 32); 0
1836 LHS = Builder.CreateShl(LHS, ShiftAmt); 0
1837 LHS = Builder.CreateAShr(LHS, ShiftAmt); 0
1838 RHS = Builder.CreateShl(RHS, ShiftAmt); 0
1839 RHS = Builder.CreateAShr(RHS, ShiftAmt); 0
1840 } else { ----
1841 // Clear the upper bits. ----
1842 Constant *Mask = ConstantInt::get(Ty, 0xffffffff); 0
1843 LHS = Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, Mask); 0
1844 RHS = Builder.CreateAnd(RHS, Mask); 0
1845 } ----
1846 ----
1847 Value *Res = Builder.CreateMul(LHS, RHS); 0
1848 ----
1849 if (CI.arg_size() == 4) 0
1850 Res = EmitX86Select(Builder, CI.getArgOperand(3), Res, CI.getArgOperand(2)); 0
1851 ----
1852 return Res; 0
1853 } ----
1854 ----
1855 // Applying mask on vector of i1's and make sure result is at least 8 bits wide. ----
1856 static Value *ApplyX86MaskOn1BitsVec(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Vec, 0
1857 Value *Mask) { ----
1858 unsigned NumElts = cast(Vec->getType())->getNumElements(); 0
1859 if (Mask) { 0
1860 const auto *C = dyn_cast(Mask); 0
1861 if (!C || !C->isAllOnesValue()) 0
1862 Vec = Builder.CreateAnd(Vec, getX86MaskVec(Builder, Mask, NumElts)); 0
1863 } ----
1864 ----
1865 if (NumElts < 8) { 0
1866 int Indices[8]; ----
1867 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) 0
1868 Indices[i] = i; 0
1869 for (unsigned i = NumElts; i != 8; ++i) 0
1870 Indices[i] = NumElts + i % NumElts; 0
1871 Vec = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, 0
1872 Constant::getNullValue(Vec->getType()), 0
1873 Indices); ----
1874 } ----
1875 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Vec, Builder.getIntNTy(std::max(NumElts, 8U))); 0
1876 } ----
1877 ----
1878 static Value *upgradeMaskedCompare(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, 0
1879 unsigned CC, bool Signed) { ----
1880 Value *Op0 = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1881 unsigned NumElts = cast(Op0->getType())->getNumElements(); 0
1882 ----
1883 Value *Cmp; ----
1884 if (CC == 3) { 0
1885 Cmp = Constant::getNullValue( 0
1886 FixedVectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), NumElts)); 0
1887 } else if (CC == 7) { 0
1888 Cmp = Constant::getAllOnesValue( 0
1889 FixedVectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), NumElts)); 0
1890 } else { ----
1891 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred; ----
1892 switch (CC) { 0
1893 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown condition code"); 0
1894 case 0: Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ; break; 0
1895 case 1: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT; break; 0
1896 case 2: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE; break; 0
1897 case 4: Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE; break; 0
1898 case 5: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE; break; 0
1899 case 6: Pred = Signed ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT; break; 0
1900 } ----
1901 Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, Op0, CI.getArgOperand(1)); 0
1902 } ----
1903 ----
1904 Value *Mask = CI.getArgOperand(CI.arg_size() - 1); 0
1905 ----
1906 return ApplyX86MaskOn1BitsVec(Builder, Cmp, Mask); 0
1907 } ----
1908 ----
1909 // Replace a masked intrinsic with an older unmasked intrinsic. ----
1910 static Value *UpgradeX86MaskedShift(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI, 0
1911 Intrinsic::ID IID) { ----
1912 Function *Intrin = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI.getModule(), IID); 0
1913 Value *Rep = Builder.CreateCall(Intrin, 0
1914 { CI.getArgOperand(0), CI.getArgOperand(1) }); 0
1915 return EmitX86Select(Builder, CI.getArgOperand(3), Rep, CI.getArgOperand(2)); 0
1916 } ----
1917 ----
1918 static Value* upgradeMaskedMove(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI) { 0
1919 Value* A = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1920 Value* B = CI.getArgOperand(1); 0
1921 Value* Src = CI.getArgOperand(2); 0
1922 Value* Mask = CI.getArgOperand(3); 0
1923 ----
1924 Value* AndNode = Builder.CreateAnd(Mask, APInt(8, 1)); 0
1925 Value* Cmp = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(AndNode); 0
1926 Value* Extract1 = Builder.CreateExtractElement(B, (uint64_t)0); 0
1927 Value* Extract2 = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Src, (uint64_t)0); 0
1928 Value* Select = Builder.CreateSelect(Cmp, Extract1, Extract2); 0
1929 return Builder.CreateInsertElement(A, Select, (uint64_t)0); 0
1930 } ----
1931 ----

1933 static Value* UpgradeMaskToInt(IRBuilder<> &Builder, CallBase &CI) { 0
1934 Value* Op = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
1935 Type* ReturnOp = CI.getType(); 0
1936 unsigned NumElts = cast(CI.getType())->getNumElements(); 0
1937 Value *Mask = getX86MaskVec(Builder, Op, NumElts); 0
1938 return Builder.CreateSExt(Mask, ReturnOp, "vpmovm2"); 0
1939 } ----

4733 if (NumOperands == 0) 0

4735 ----

4757 Instruction *llvm::UpgradeBitCastInst(unsigned Opc, Value *V, Type *DestTy, 0
4758 Instruction *&Temp) { ----
4759 if (Opc != Instruction::BitCast) 0
4760 return nullptr; 0
4761 ----
4762 Temp = nullptr; 0
4763 Type *SrcTy = V->getType(); 0
4764 if (SrcTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && DestTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && 0
4765 SrcTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != DestTy->getPointerAddressSpace()) { 0
4766 LLVMContext &Context = V->getContext(); 0
4767 ----
4768 // We have no information about target data layout, so we assume that ----
4769 // the maximum pointer size is 64bit. ----
4770 Type *MidTy = Type::getInt64Ty(Context); 0
4771 Temp = CastInst::Create(Instruction::PtrToInt, V, MidTy); 0
4772 ----
4773 return CastInst::Create(Instruction::IntToPtr, Temp, DestTy); 0
4774 } ----
4775 ----
4776 return nullptr; 0
4777 } ----

4828 /// This checks for objc retain release marker which should be upgraded. It ----

4830 static bool UpgradeRetainReleaseMarker(Module &M) { 0
4831 bool Changed = false; 0
4832 const char *MarkerKey = "clang.arc.retainAutoreleasedReturnValueMarker"; 0
4833 NamedMDNode *ModRetainReleaseMarker = M.getNamedMetadata(MarkerKey); 0
4834 if (ModRetainReleaseMarker) { 0
4835 MDNode *Op = ModRetainReleaseMarker->getOperand(0); 0
4836 if (Op) { 0
4837 MDString *ID = dyn_cast_or_null(Op->getOperand(0)); 0
4838 if (ID) { 0
4839 SmallVector ValueComp; 0
4840 ID->getString().split(ValueComp, "#"); 0
4841 if (ValueComp.size() == 2) { 0
4842 std::string NewValue = ValueComp[0].str() + ";" + ValueComp[1].str(); 0
4843 ID = MDString::get(M.getContext(), NewValue); 0
4844 } 0
4845 M.addModuleFlag(Module::Error, MarkerKey, ID); 0
4846 M.eraseNamedMetadata(ModRetainReleaseMarker); 0
4847 Changed = true; 0
4848 } 0
4849 } ----
4850 } ----
4851 return Changed; 0
4852 } ----

4854 void llvm::UpgradeARCRuntime(Module &M) { 0
4855 // This lambda converts normal function calls to ARC runtime functions to ----
4856 // intrinsic calls. ----
4857 auto UpgradeToIntrinsic = [&](const char *OldFunc, 0
4858 llvm::Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicFunc) { ----
4859 Function *Fn = M.getFunction(OldFunc); 0
4860 ----
4861 if (!Fn) 0
4862 return; 0
4863 ----
4864 Function *NewFn = llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(&M, IntrinsicFunc); 0
4865 ----
4866 for (User *U : make_early_inc_range(Fn->users())) { 0
4867 CallInst *CI = dyn_cast(U); 0
4868 if (!CI || CI->getCalledFunction() != Fn) 0
4869 continue; 0
4870 ----
4871 IRBuilder<> Builder(CI->getParent(), CI->getIterator()); 0
4872 FunctionType *NewFuncTy = NewFn->getFunctionType(); 0
4873 SmallVector Args; 0
4874 ----
4875 // Don't upgrade the intrinsic if it's not valid to bitcast the return ----
4876 // value to the return type of the old function. ----
4877 if (NewFuncTy->getReturnType() != CI->getType() && 0
4878 !CastInst::castIsValid(Instruction::BitCast, CI, 0
4879 NewFuncTy->getReturnType())) ----
4880 continue; 0
4881 ----
4882 bool InvalidCast = false; 0
4883 ----
4884 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CI->arg_size(); I != E; ++I) { 0
4885 Value *Arg = CI->getArgOperand(I); 0
4886 ----
4887 // Bitcast argument to the parameter type of the new function if it's ----
4888 // not a variadic argument. ----
4889 if (I < NewFuncTy->getNumParams()) { 0
4890 // Don't upgrade the intrinsic if it's not valid to bitcast the argument ----
4891 // to the parameter type of the new function. ----
4892 if (!CastInst::castIsValid(Instruction::BitCast, Arg, 0
4893 NewFuncTy->getParamType(I))) { ----
4894 InvalidCast = true; 0

5138 namespace { ----
5139 // Prior to LLVM 10.0, the strictfp attribute could be used on individual ----
5140 // callsites within a function that did not also have the strictfp attribute. ----
5141 // Since 10.0, if strict FP semantics are needed within a function, the ----
5142 // function must have the strictfp attribute and all calls within the function ----
5143 // must also have the strictfp attribute. This latter restriction is ----
5144 // necessary to prevent unwanted libcall simplification when a function is ----
5145 // being cloned (such as for inlining). ----
5146 // ----
5147 // The "dangling" strictfp attribute usage was only used to prevent constant ----
5148 // folding and other libcall simplification. The nobuiltin attribute on the ----
5149 // callsite has the same effect. ----
5150 struct StrictFPUpgradeVisitor : public InstVisitor { ----
5151 StrictFPUpgradeVisitor() = default; ----
5152 ----
5153 void visitCallBase(CallBase &Call) { 0
5154 if (!Call.isStrictFP()) 0
5155 return; 0
5156 if (isa(&Call)) 0
5157 return; 0
5158 // If we get here, the caller doesn't have the strictfp attribute ----
5159 // but this callsite does. Replace the strictfp attribute with nobuiltin. ----
5160 Call.removeFnAttr(Attribute::StrictFP); 0
5161 Call.addFnAttr(Attribute::NoBuiltin); 0
5162 } ----
5163 }; ----
5164 } // namespace ----
5165 ----
5166 void llvm::UpgradeFunctionAttributes(Function &F) { 0
5167 // If a function definition doesn't have the strictfp attribute, ----
5168 // convert any callsite strictfp attributes to nobuiltin. ----
5169 if (!F.isDeclaration() && !F.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::StrictFP)) { 0
5170 StrictFPUpgradeVisitor SFPV; ----
5171 SFPV.visit(F); 0
5172 } ----
5173 ----
5174 // Remove all incompatibile attributes from function. ----
5175 F.removeRetAttrs(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(F.getReturnType())); 0
5176 for (auto &Arg : F.args()) 0
5177 Arg.removeAttrs(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(Arg.getType())); 0
5178 } 0

5243 Triple T(TT); 0

5245 // space of globals to 1. ----

5258 ----

5260 // AMDGCN data layout upgrades. ----
5261 if (T.isAMDGCN()) { 0
5262 // Define address spaces for constants. ----

5278 Res.append("-p7:160:256:256:32"); 0

5280 Res.append("-p8:128:128"); 0

5282 return Res; 0
5283 } ----
5284 ----
5285 if (!T.isX86()) 0
5286 return Res; 0
5287 ----
5288 // If the datalayout matches the expected format, add pointer size address ----
5289 // spaces to the datalayout. ----
